---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Ireland Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/ireland/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'UK for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/uk' },
  { title: 'France for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/france' },
  { title: 'Spain for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/spain' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'irelandFit', header: 'Ireland Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€380-540/mo', irelandFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€340-480/mo', irelandFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€310-440/mo', irelandFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'AXA Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€290-420/mo', irelandFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Irish VHI/Laya', entryAge: 'No limit', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€150-400/mo', irelandFit: 'Local Option' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: '€310-480', annual: '€3,720-5,760' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: '€430-650', annual: '€5,160-7,800' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: '€580-880', annual: '€6,960-10,560' },
  { category: 'Irish Private Health Insurance', monthly: '€150-400', annual: '€1,800-4,800' },
  { category: 'HSE Public (Residents)', monthly: 'Free (income-based)', annual: 'Tax-funded' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Ireland 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Ireland. HSE public healthcare, Dublin hospitals, visa requirements, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Ireland"
  subheadline="Ireland offers English-speaking culture, friendly communities, and EU membership—with public healthcare access for residents."
  heroImage="/images/countries/ireland-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/bupa-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Ireland</h2>
  <p>
    Ireland offers a unique combination: English-speaking European Union membership, friendly locals, stunning landscapes, and access to both EU healthcare and Irish public services. For American retirees with Irish heritage, the ancestral connection adds emotional appeal.
  </p>

  <p>
    Dublin provides excellent hospitals and cultural activities. Cork offers a more relaxed pace with good healthcare. Galway on the west coast has dramatic scenery and a strong arts community. Smaller towns throughout Ireland offer affordable living with adequate medical access.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Good quality; HSE public system + private options</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> English (Irish Gaelic co-official)</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> €2,000-3,500/month; Dublin most expensive</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Mild but wet; no extreme temperatures</li>
      <li><strong>EU Status:</strong> Full EU member; not Schengen (separate border controls)</li>
      <li><strong>Culture:</strong> Welcoming, pub culture, strong sense of community</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Ireland's Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Ireland's Health Service Executive (HSE) provides public healthcare. It's tax-funded and free for those with medical cards (means-tested) or GP visit cards (for those over 70). Those without cards pay for GP visits (€50-70) but get free public hospital treatment.
  </p>

  <p>
    Private healthcare is popular for faster access. About 45% of Irish residents have private health insurance. Private hospitals like the Blackrock Clinic and Beacon Hospital offer shorter wait times and choice of consultants.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Wait Times Warning</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      HSE public hospital wait times can be long for non-urgent procedures—sometimes 12-24 months for certain surgeries. Emergency care is immediate, but elective procedures benefit significantly from private insurance.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Ireland offers several pathways for non-EU seniors:
  </p>

  <h3>Stamp 0 Visa (Retired Person of Independent Means)</h3>
  <p>
    For retirees with minimum €50,000 annual income and €100,000 in savings. Must have comprehensive private health insurance. Renewable annually, doesn't lead to citizenship but allows long-term residence.
  </p>

  <h3>Stamp 4 via Marriage/Civil Partnership</h3>
  <p>
    If married to an Irish citizen, you can apply for residence. After 3 years of marriage and residence, you may apply for citizenship.
  </p>

  <h3>Irish Ancestry</h3>
  <p>
    If you have an Irish-born grandparent, you may claim Irish citizenship through the Foreign Births Register. This grants full EU citizenship and all associated rights.
  </p>

  <h3>EU Citizens</h3>
  <p>
    EU citizens can move freely to Ireland. Register with immigration and access HSE healthcare. Those over 70 receive free GP visit cards.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements vary by visa type:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Stamp 0 visa:</strong> Comprehensive private health insurance mandatory</li>
    <li><strong>Other visas:</strong> Proof of healthcare access required</li>
    <li><strong>EU citizens:</strong> EHIC valid initially; register for HSE access</li>
    <li><strong>Over 70:</strong> Free GP visit card regardless of income</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Ireland</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      Most non-EU seniors need private insurance for visa purposes. Irish private health insurance (VHI, Laya, Irish Life) is often more affordable than international insurance once you're resident. Many combine: Irish private for local care, international for travel and potential evacuation.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Ireland, both international and local providers offer strong options:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Ireland</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), strong Irish presence (owns Laya Healthcare)</li>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Good Irish network, international flexibility</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Competitive European pricing</li>
    <li><strong>Irish VHI/Laya:</strong> Local options once resident; community-rated (no age loading)</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage and pricing from providers that accept seniors for Ireland.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs in Ireland are moderate compared to international options:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Irish providers:</strong> VHI, Laya, Irish Life often cheaper than international once resident</li>
    <li><strong>Community rating:</strong> Irish insurers can't charge more based on age (but can have waiting periods)</li>
    <li><strong>GP visit card:</strong> Free for over 70s, reducing routine care costs</li>
    <li><strong>Higher excess:</strong> €500-1,000 excess reduces premiums significantly</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American with Irish Heritage, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Irish-born grandmother qualifies for citizenship. Retiring to Cork.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Claim Irish citizenship first. As citizen, access HSE healthcare. Add Irish private insurance (Laya) for faster private care.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Laya ~€200/month. Full citizen rights including EU healthcare access.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: Canadian Retiree, 71</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> No Irish connections. Has €60,000/year pension. Wants Stamp 0 visa.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global for visa requirement. Meets income threshold. Can switch to Irish provider after 1 year.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~€480/month BUPA initially. Irish VHI after transition ~€250/month.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: British Couple, Both 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Post-Brexit, moving to Galway. One has COPD.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global initially. Irish system covers pre-existing once resident. Transition to Irish VHI.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~€900/month combined initially. Irish VHI ~€400/month combined (community-rated).</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I access free healthcare in Ireland as a retiree?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Residents are entitled to public hospital care through the HSE. Those over 70 automatically receive GP visit cards for free doctor visits. Medical cards (covering more) are means-tested. Stamp 0 visa holders typically don't qualify for public healthcare, hence the private insurance requirement.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What's the difference between Irish health insurers?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        VHI is the oldest and largest. Laya Healthcare (owned by BUPA) offers competitive plans. Irish Life Health is newer but competitive. All are community-rated—they can't charge you more for being older. Compare plans based on hospital coverage and excess levels.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How do I claim Irish citizenship through ancestry?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        If you have an Irish-born grandparent, you can apply through the Foreign Births Register. You'll need birth certificates, marriage certificates, and other documents proving lineage. The process takes 6-12 months and costs about €280. Success grants full Irish (and EU) citizenship.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Ireland expensive for retirees?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Dublin is expensive (comparable to London for housing). Outside Dublin, costs are more reasonable. Healthcare costs with private insurance are moderate. Food and utilities are slightly higher than European average. Many retirees find smaller towns like Killarney, Sligo, or Westport offer good value.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers that specialize in senior expat coverage for Ireland.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Irish authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
